metadata.name: Sapura Energy Berhad
metadata.description: Sapura Energy Berhad, an investment holding company, offers integrated oil and gas services and solutions in Malaysia, Asia, Turkey, Australia, the Americas, the Middle East, Africa, and internationally. It operates through Engineering and Construction, Drilling, and Exploration and Production segments. The company provides engineering, procurement, construction, and commissioning services. It offers installation of offshore platforms, marine pipelines, subsea facilities, umbilicals, risers, and flowlines; transportation and installation services for heavy lift, pipeline installation, jacket launch, floatover, and deepwater projects; diving and related underwater works; subsea engineering and construction services; and hook-up and commissioning services for new greenfield facilities in the oil and gas industry, as well as designs, manufactures, and operates remotely operated vehicles. The company also provides well intervention and decommissioning services; and operation and maintenance services comprising topside maintenance, subsea, brownfield rejuvenation, geo survey and geotechnical, and other services, as well as owns and operates a fleet of offshore support vessels. In addition, it owns and operates tender assist drilling and semi-tender rigs. Further, the company engages in the exploration and production of oil and gas in Malaysia. Additionally, it engages in the development of marine technology and marine chartering activities; and provision of technical consulting services, and advanced subsea and floating systems. The company was formerly known as SapuraKencana Petroleum Berhad and changed its name to Sapura Energy Berhad in March 2017. The company is headquartered in Seri Kembangan, Malaysia.
